00:14:46.716 --> 00:14:50.656
B, which has been impossible using traditional inhibitors

248
00:14:50.716 --> 00:14:52.096
or PROTAC approaches?

249
00:14:53.196 --> 00:14:53.416
And

250
00:14:54.416 --> 00:14:57.856
started by a screen, and what's interesting here is that there is a single

251
00:14:57.916 --> 00:15:01.106
compound in the entire data set that initially showed

252
00:15:01.956 --> 00:15:05.776
degradation of KAT2A. Encouragingly, it was

253
00:15:05.896 --> 00:15:08.035
already out of the gate selective for B.

254
00:15:10.556 --> 00:15:14.536
It also worked as a small molecule degrader

255
00:15:14.996 --> 00:15:18.616
in all the canonical ways. So it's dependent on cereblon, it's

256
00:15:18.636 --> 00:15:22.596
dependent on the proteasome system, and the minimally reconstituted

257
00:15:22.606 --> 00:15:26.136
system in vitro using just the ligase E1, E2,

258
00:15:26.216 --> 00:15:29.876
ATP, and ubiquitin is sufficient to get ubiquitination

259
00:15:29.956 --> 00:15:31.016
off of KAT2A.

260
00:15:33.216 --> 00:15:37.196
Hundreds of compounds later, that really was driven by

261
00:15:37.496 --> 00:15:38.976
Mong, and Sam was this

262
00:15:39.916 --> 00:15:42.696
partner in crime for all the biology and biochemistry and structures,

