00:15:44.285 --> 00:15:45.456
led to a compound with

264
00:15:46.656 --> 00:15:48.516
good potency and efficacy

265
00:15:49.476 --> 00:15:53.276
by retaining all of the selectivity for KAT2A and dialing out

266
00:15:53.436 --> 00:15:56.276
the undesired effects such as GSPD1 degradation.

267
00:15:56.336 --> 00:15:59.496
So this now is a clean, selective degrader of KAT2A,

268
00:16:00.596 --> 00:16:04.396
leads to downstream downregulation of H3K9

269
00:16:04.436 --> 00:16:08.296
acetyl, which you would expect, and really doesn't recruit anything.

270
00:16:08.356 --> 00:16:10.496
So on the left, you see global proteomics.

271
00:16:10.576 --> 00:16:13.016
There's no degradation of GSPD1 or GSPD2.

272
00:16:13.616 --> 00:16:17.256
No other off targets. On the right, you see affinity purification mass spec,

273
00:16:17.496 --> 00:16:19.876
same thing, selective recruitment of KAT2A.

274
00:16:19.996 --> 00:16:22.116
So really selective chemical probe.

275
00:16:22.956 --> 00:16:26.926
And one of the reasons we were so interested is because there's been a lot

276
00:16:26.956 --> 00:16:30.716
of talk about this target out there, and there's a lot of notion that you need

